    "For instance, an incident on March 20, 2023, involving ChatGPT Plus, is a potent reminder of these risks.",
    "Service users reported seeing sensitive information from other users on their user interface, including chat logs, names, email addresses, and payment details.",
    "OpenAI, the company behind ChatGPT, traced the source of the problem to an issue with the redis-py client library, which resulted in user requests being erroneously returned to other users.",
    "This led to an immediate shutdown of ChatGPT until the issue was resolved [22] [23].",
